pWith</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">x_1</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAppend.hAppend\">++</a> <span class=\"fn\">x_1</span></span></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">::</a> <span class=\"fn\">l</span></span>)</span>.tails</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">::</a> <span class=\"fn\">l</span></span>)</span>.inits</span></span>)</span>.dropLast</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.lean#L557-L558","name":"List.cyclicPermutations_nil","line":557,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.html#List.cyclicPermutations_nil","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.html#List.cyclicPermutations_nil\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">cyclicPermutations_nil</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">[]</span>.cyclicPermutations</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">[]</span>]</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.lean#L551-L553","name":"List.cyclicPermutations","line":551,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.html#List.cyclicPermutations","doc":"List of all cyclic permutations of `l`.\nThe `cyclicPermutations` of a nonempty list `l` will always contain `List.length l` elements.\nThis implies that under certain conditions, there are duplicates in `List.cyclicPermutations l`.\nThe `n`th entry is equal to `l.rotate n`, proven in `List.get_cyclicPermutations`.\nThe proof that every cyclic permutant of `l` is in the list is `List.mem_cyclicPermutations_iff`.\n\n     cyclicPermutations [1, 2, 3, 2, 4] =\n       [[1, 2, 3, 2, 4], [2, 3, 2, 4, 1], [3, 2, 4, 1, 2],\n        [2, 4, 1, 2, 3], [4, 1, 2, 3, 2]] "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.html#List.cyclicPermutations\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">cyclicPermutations</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.lean#L535-L539","name":"List.IsRotated.map","line":535,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.html#List.IsRotated.map","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.html#List.IsRotated.map\">